GDScript

GDScript is the main scripting language for the Godot Engine that appears to the engine that will be used for the Nacirema engine currently
as the unofficial engine for the first game. The engine is a really good engine that is known to be developed by Juan Linietsky and Ariel Manzur

The scripting language is similar to Python that all scripting languages appear complex, so learning a scripting language is fun to learn from
an engine that a game is using a specific game engine. The multiple codes involved with producing the desired commands or effects in a game
such as Nacirema is with the Node type development inside the Godot Engine. The Node code is a funny term and easy to understand when you see
the node functionality in the program. The nodes are a basic circular design that have lines that connect the dots for the functionality of
a desired position of an object in the game

